If the camera in The Last of Us feels too zoomed out or too far, there are a few ways to adjust or control the zoom depending on what you mean. 🎮

1. While Playing (Aiming Zoom)
Press L2 / Left Trigger to aim your weapon.

The camera will zoom in automatically when aiming. 🔍

2. Change Camera Distance in Settings
In The Last of Us Part I or The Last of Us Part II you can adjust camera settings:

Open Options / Settings

Go to Camera

Change:

Camera Distance

Field of View (FOV)

Suggested values:

Lower FOV (70–80) → More zoomed in

Higher FOV (90+) → More zoomed out

3. Accessibility Camera Zoom
The game also has Accessibility Zoom:

Go to Options

Open Accessibility

Turn on Zoom

Use the touchpad or button combo to zoom in.

4. If You Mean When Making a Game Like The Last of Us
If you are creating your own Last-of-Us style game, you fix zoom by changing the camera FOV or camera position in the game engine.

